+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_014uyBEwALPFYC2mVufmQaP3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Non-interactive mode: using Autopilot. Let me work through the design decisions rapidly.\n\n**Design decisions for this problem:**\n\n1. **Algorithm**: Gaussian elimination over finite fields — GF(2) for toggle, GF(p) for counter. This is the standard efficient approach for these linear algebra problems over finite fields.\n\n2. **Architecture**: Single `src/index.ts` file with both functions plus shared Gaussian elimination utility. The problem is self-contained and doesn't warrant multiple files.\n\n3. **Lexicographic minimality**: After row reduction, free variables can be set to minimize total presses and break ties lexicographically. We enumerate free variable combinations (for GF(2) there are at most 2^(free vars) combinations, bounded by the matrix size of 40).\n\n4. **Minimum presses selection**: For toggle (GF(2)), minimize count of 1s. For counter (GF(p)), minimize sum of presses, then lexicographic order.\n\nLet me proceed directly to implementation via TDD."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":142,"cache_read_input_tokens":24669,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":142},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"48375e3e-d5d7-49ac-a68d-a808e5eee6a0","uuid":"0d0e5ea7-2bf6-483c-aafa-d6eb0e9df824"}
